HEADWORD: Dellacruscan
<hw>Del`la*crus"can</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or
pertaining to the Accademia della Crusca in Florence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>The Dellacruscan School</b></col>, <cd>a name given in
satire to a class of affected English writers, most of whom lived in
Florence, about <sc>a. d.</sc> 1785.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

